            <title>[PIG-3495] Streaming udf e2e tests failures on Windows</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3495</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Register a jython script with an absolute path fail. For Example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;register &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;D:\scriptingudf.py&apos;&lt;/span&gt; using jython as myfuncs;
a = load &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;studenttab10k&apos;&lt;/span&gt; using PigStorage() as (name, age:&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, gpa:&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;double&lt;/span&gt;);
b = foreach a generate myfuncs.square(age);
dump b;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
